                            <comment id="13020323" author="hudson" created="Fri, 15 Apr 2011 16:23:23 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Mahout-Quality #751 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Mahout-Quality/751/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Mahout-Quality/751/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    First step on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-664&quot; title=&quot;Remove usage of XStream string serialization too?&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-664&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-664&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, remove redundant use of Xstream&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13037272" author="adeneche" created="Sat, 21 May 2011 06:42:14 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I will have to take a closer look to the watchmaker code, but for df I know I used StringUtils to serialize some implementation of TreeBuilder, for now it&apos;s just DefaultTreeBuilder but it can be a custom implementation too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13042770" author="srowen" created="Thu, 2 Jun 2011 14:32:42 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I can&apos;t really get any farther on this issue since removing XStream would mean removing serialization of TreeBuilder and FitnessEvaluator, and the way the code is structured it does require it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We could use Writable, or accept a use of Serializable here, except that the result needs to be a String. that can be base-64 encoded, but then I wonder if it&apos;s getting too weird? versus keeping the dependency on XPP and Xstream just for this. I really don&apos;t know, any thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13044576" author="srowen" created="Sun, 5 Jun 2011 17:52:18 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I give up, I don&apos;t think there is way to meaningfully finish this, so, having removed the superfluous usages, am calling it a day.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
